<h1 class="hero-h">Fractional CMO Austin TX <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Austin-based, working with B2B operators here.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Treetop is based in Austin and works with B2B mid-market companies across Texas. If you're a B2B founder or CEO between $3M and $30M ARR considering a fractional CMO, here's the Austin-specific context and how to think about the engagement.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Treetop offers fractional CMO services in Austin, TX and across Texas. Engagements typically run $8K-$25K/month for B2B mid-market companies needing senior marketing leadership without a full-time hire. We work in-person in Austin and remote elsewhere.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Why Austin's B2B market is unique</h2><p class="body">Austin's B2B ecosystem in 2026 is meaningfully different from the Silicon Valley playbook. The market is larger and more diverse than it gets credit for: strong SaaS scene, but also financial services, logistics, professional services, healthcare tech, and growing manufacturing/industrial B2B.</p><p class="body">Practical implications for marketing leadership:</p><ul class="ul"><li>Buyers expect more substance, less hype. Bay Area marketing speak lands flatter here.</li><li>Talent market is mid-sized but high quality. Strong fractional and operator pool.</li><li>Capital is patient enough to allow real strategy, but operators expect ROI on a defined timeline.</li><li>The market is large enough to test ideas locally, small enough to know who's doing what.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional CMO vs. full-time hire vs. agency: an Austin market comparison</h2>
<p class="body">Austin B2B founders often evaluate three options when marketing leadership becomes a bottleneck. Here's how they compare on the dimensions that matter most for a $3M-$30M ARR company.</p>
<table class="cmp-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Factor</th>
      <th>Fractional CMO</th>
      <th>Full-Time CMO Hire</th>
      <th>Marketing Agency</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
