<p class="body">The pattern in Austin: founders at $5M-$15M ARR hire an agency first, hit a ceiling because there's no strategy layer, then bring in a fractional CMO to own the full picture. Starting with the fractional CMO skips that expensive detour.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Treetop's Austin engagement model</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>In-person where it matters.</strong> Kickoff in person; quarterly on-site; otherwise structured remote rhythm.</li><li><strong>1-2 days per week typical.</strong> Fractional means fractional: defined cadence, not always-on.</li><li><strong>Builder profile.</strong> We ship work; we don't just present strategy.</li><li><strong>AI-fluent.</strong> Modern fractional CMO work compounds with AI workflows. We bring those.</li><li><strong>12-18 month commitments</strong> typical for compounding outcomes.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to consider Treetop specifically</h2><ul class="ul"><li>You're a B2B founder/CEO at $3M-$30M ARR.</li><li>You're in or willing to engage with Austin or Central Texas.</li><li>You want senior marketing leadership without a $300K+ full-time hire.</li><li>You want a fractional CMO who personally uses AI tooling, not just talks about it.</li><li>You can commit \$8K-\$25K/month for 12-18 months.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Specific Austin/Texas markets we work in</h2><ul class="ul"><li>B2B SaaS: Austin is dense with mid-market SaaS that fits our profile.</li><li>Financial services / fintech: strong Austin presence.</li><li>Healthcare tech: growing rapidly here.</li><li>Logistics, supply chain B2B: meaningful Texas-specific clusters.</li><li>Professional services firms: consulting, legal, accounting, architecture.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How much does a fractional CMO cost in Austin, TX?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Fractional CMO engagements in Austin typically range from $8,000 to $25,000 per month depending on time commitment and scope. Most B2B mid-market engagements run 1-2 days per week over a 12-18 month period. This compares to $250,000-$350,000 annually for a full-time CMO hire when you include salary, benefits, and equity.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is Treetop Austin-based?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes. Treetop is based in Austin, TX. Bill Colbert, the founder, lives and works in Austin. Austin-area clients typically get in-person kickoffs and quarterly on-site sessions, with structured remote rhythm in between.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you work with companies outside Austin?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes. We work with B2B mid-market companies across Texas and remotely with US-based clients. In-person is available for Austin and Central Texas; remote engagements follow the same structured cadence.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What's a typical fractional CMO engagement cost?</h3><p class="faq-qa">\$8K-\$25K/month depending on time commitment and scope. Typically 12-18 month engagements.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How is a fractional CMO different from a marketing agency?</h3><p class="faq-qa">A fractional CMO sits inside your leadership team and owns strategy, pipeline, and revenue outcomes. An agency executes specific channels (ads, SEO, content) but rarely owns full go-to-market strategy or sits in leadership meetings. If you need strategy and execution ownership, a fractional CMO is the right fit.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you offer fractional CRO services too?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes. Fractional CRO engagements are available for B2B companies whose sales, CS, and RevOps alignment is broken. CRO and CMO work often overlap at the $5M-$20M ARR stage.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How do I start an engagement?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Book the \$1,500 AI Audit as a low-commitment first engagement. It produces a written, prioritized marketing roadmap in 5 business days. Alternatively, schedule a call to discuss fit and scope directly.</p></div>
</div></section>

